Governor Ugwuanyi of Enugu State has urged Christian faithful  to use Christmas for sustained prayers for God’s intervention on Nigeria’s challenges. Ugwuanyi said this in his Christmas message in Enugu on Friday. The governor urged Nigerians not to lose faith in God in the face of adversity, but to remain committed to the good news that Jesus Christ was born to bring salvation to mankind. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! He stressed that the yuletide offered Nigerians the opportunity to reflect soberly, pray for the country and its leaders. “This is a period to engage in activities that promote peace, unity, security and progress of Nigeria”, he said. Yuletide: Kwara Speaker Tasks Nigerians On COVID-19 Safety Measures Yuletide Message: JIFORM Charges Nations To Temper Governance With Love For Migrants The governor also thanked the people of the state for their love, goodwill, solidarity, support and unceasing prayers. Ugwuanyi reassured of his firm resolve to sustain the tempo of peace and good governance in the state as well as to continue to serve the people with the fear of God. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION